    category: 'AIEO',
    location: 'General',
    readTime: '11 min',
    excerpt: 'AI tools are answering your customers\' questions. Here\'s how to make sure your brand is the answer they give.',
    content: `<p>When a potential customer asks ChatGPT for recommendations in your category, or asks Perplexity to find the best provider of your service in their city, your brand is either in the answer or it isn't. In 2026, that binary is becoming as commercially important as whether you rank on page one of Google. Here's how to improve your brand's probability of being cited by the major AI tools.</p>
<h2>Understand the AI Citation Ecosystem</h2>
<p>ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity all work differently. ChatGPT in its base form draws from training data - information available on the web up to its knowledge cutoff. ChatGPT with Browse and Perplexity search the web in real time and cite sources. Google's AI Overviews draw from Google's search index. Each of these systems weights different signals, which means that a comprehensive AI citation strategy addresses all of them, not just one.</p>
<h2>Build Entity Consistency Across the Web</h2>
<p>AI systems learn about brands by synthesising information from many sources. If your brand name, location, description, services, and founding information are described inconsistently across your website, LinkedIn, Crunchbase, industry directories, and press mentions, the AI's model of your brand is uncertain and less likely to be cited with confidence. Auditing and correcting entity information across all sources is a foundational AIEO step.</p>
<h2>Earn Coverage in Sources AI Tools Trust</h2>
<p>AI language models and real-time search systems weight some sources more heavily than others. Being featured or mentioned in major industry publications, in Wikipedia (where eligible), in Google's Knowledge Graph, and in the authoritative sources of your vertical significantly increases the likelihood of AI citation. Earned media is a core AIEO tactic, not just a PR exercise.</p>
<h2>Create Question-Answering Content</h2>
<p>Structure your content to answer specific questions that your target customers ask AI tools. "What is the best [service] in [city]?" queries are commonly directed at AI tools. Content that answers these questions comprehensively - with specific, verifiable information - is more likely to be incorporated into AI-generated answers than content that talks about your brand in promotional terms.</p>
<h2>Measure AI Visibility</h2>
<p>Track how your brand appears across AI tools regularly. Query ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini, and Google's AI Overviews for your category and location at least monthly. Document what these tools say about your brand and your competitors. Use this intelligence to guide your content strategy, earned media priorities, and entity optimization work. SA Media builds AI visibility tracking into all AIEO programs for clients.</p>`,
